          <li><a href="https://psycnet.apa.org/record/1989-25692-001" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mitchell, Russo & Pennington (1989) — Back to the Future: Temporal Perspective in the Explanation of Events (<em>Journal of Behavioral Decision Making</em>)</a> — The foundational research demonstrating that prospective hindsight — the cognitive mechanism behind the pre-mortem — increases the identification of failure causes by approximately 30% over standard forecasting approaches.</li>
